GitHub offers plans for free, professional, and enterprise accounts.[5] Free GitHub accounts are commonly used to host open source projects.[6] As of January 2019, GitHub offers unlimited private repositories to all plans, including free accounts.[7] As of May 2019, GitHub reports having over 37 million users[8] and more than 100 million repositories[9] (including at least 28 million public repositories),[10] making it the largest host of source code in the world.[11:w
